Task: Weekly cronjob to delete log files older than 7 days.

Step1
Check the log path and logs for apache2.
Command: cd /var/log/apache2/
 
Step 2
Create the script file named ‘del’ to delete log files older than 7 days.

Step 3
Set up a cronjob with crontab for weekly execution.
Command: crontab -e
Select the editor and add following line in the crontab file.
0 16 * * 6 /del
  
Note: Runs every Saturday at 6 PM to execute ‘del’ script.







 

